31. You can convert a Text Area(Long) to Email, Phone, Text, Text Area or URL without data loss.

**A.True**

B.False

[https://help.salesforce.com/s/articleView?id=sf.notes_on_changing_custom_field_types.htm&type=5](https://help.salesforce.com/s/articleView?id=sf.notes_on_changing_custom_field_types.htm&type=5)

> Only convert custom fields that thereâ€™s no data for or you risk losing your data. Changing the data type of an existing custom field can cause data loss in these situations:
> 

> Changing from Text Area (Long) to any type except Email, Phone, Text, Text Area, or URL
> 
> 
> 

When you convert a long text area field to an Email, Phone, Text, Text Area, or URL type field, the record data is truncated to the first 255 characters of the field.(ì´ ë¶€ë¶„ì— ë”°ë¼ì„œ Bê°€ ì •ë‹µì´ì§€ ì•Šì„ê¹Œ ìƒê°í•©ë‹ˆë‹¤)

32.You cannot change auto number to text and vice versa and not loose your data.(31ë²ˆê³¼ ë¹„ìŠ·)

A.True

**B.False**

> If you convert an **auto-number field** into a text field, the data in that field remains unchanged. Also, you can safely convert a text custom field into an auto-number field without losing your data. **Converting an auto-number field into any other data type results in data loss**. Auto-number fields can contain a maximum of 30 characters. Before converting a text custom field into an auto-number field, change any records that contain more than 30 characters in that field.
> 

33.If data is lost, any list view based on the custom field will be deleted, and **assignment and escalation rules** may be affected.(27ë²ˆê³¼ ì—°ê³„í•´ì„œ ê³µë¶€í•˜ê¸°)

**A. True**

B. False

